place.name: WEETHLEY
place.gazetteerText: WEETHLEY, a parish in Alcester district, Warwick; 3 miles SW of Alcester r. station. Post town, Alcester, under Redditch. Acres, 638. Real property, £616. Pop., 33. Houses, 9. The living is a p. curacy, annexed to Kinwarton. The church was rebuilt in 1858. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
